gimme that bass ♪

13:49.792 --> 13:52.708
♪ Gimme gimme gimme
I've been gone for too long ♪

13:52.708 --> 13:55.917
♪ Now it's time
I take it back ♪

13:55.917 --> 13:57.542
[knocking]

14:08.417 --> 14:09.959
- Hi.
- Marti.

14:09.959 --> 14:12.959
- What are you doing here?
- I needed to talk to you.

14:12.959 --> 14:15.250
You got my text, right?

14:15.250 --> 14:17.667
Yeah. I did. Um, that's,
that's not why I'm here.

14:17.667 --> 14:19.333
Listen, I wanna explain,
but I can't right now.

14:19.333 --> 14:21.625
I'm kind of busy.

14:25.667 --> 14:28.792
Uh, you're-you're
with someone, okay, uh..

14:28.792 --> 14:31.125
- I got it loud and clear.
- 'Come on, I'm waiting.'

14:31.125 --> 14:32.875
Hi.

14:34.417 --> 14:36.583
Uh, hi yourself.

14:36.583 --> 14:40.000
You have pretty hair.

14:40.708 --> 14:43.500
[chuckles]
This is Nikki.

14:43.500 --> 14:45.458
It's my daughter.

14:49.250 --> 14:51.209
Well, uh..

14:55.166 --> 14:56.708
[instrumental music]

14:58.209 --> 15:00.291
You have a kid.

15:00.291 --> 15:02.250
How did I not know this?

15:02.250 --> 15:03.917
How did I not know
you're married?

15:03.917 --> 15:06.208
I'm legally separated.
The divorce is pending.

15:06.208 --> 15:08.125
[chuckles]
Don't lawyer me.

15:08.125 --> 15:10.083
My ex had an emergency
last night

15:10.083 --> 15:11.959
and she had to drop Nikki off.

15:11.959 --> 15:14.167
You could have told me this
before we, you know, started..

15:14.167 --> 15:17.959
Yeah, well, I tried,
but your tongue
was in my mouth.

15:19.291 --> 15:22.000
I bet you crack 'em up
in the courtroom, huh?

15:22.000 --> 15:23.959
Mm-hmm.

15:23.959 --> 15:25.625
Anyhow, now that I know

15:25.625 --> 15:28.375
maybe the three of us
grab brunch?

15:28.375 --> 15:31.417
Not advisable, sorry.

15:31.417 --> 15:33.250
- My therapist suggests--
- Your therapist?

15:33.250 --> 15:36.209
My therapist suggests
a six-month waiting period

15:36.209 --> 15:40.625
before introducing Nikki
to any sort of girlfriend

15:40.625 --> 15:43.291
potential girlfriend
'cause if it doesn't work out

15:43.291 --> 15:45.917
then you leave or we split up

15:45.917 --> 15:48.333
Nikki's gonna be that
much less emotionally open

15:48.333 --> 15:51.125
to the next woman
that I bring into my life.

15:52.250 --> 15:54.375
Already on to
the next woman, are we?

15:54.375 --> 15:57.209
Yeah, I didn't mean that
the way it sounded.

15:57.209 --> 15:58.708
It's okay.

16:00.042 --> 16:02.708
You're, uh, looking out
for your kid, I get that.

16:05.208 --> 16:08.042
It's attractive.

16:08.042 --> 16:10.209
Dad, we need more cereal.

16:10.209 --> 16:13.375
Okay, one second, honey.

16:13.375 --> 16:17.000
Let me make it up to you
by cooking you dinner tonight.

16:19.792 --> 16:22.792
How does that sound?

16:22.792 --> 16:24.875
It sounds fantastic.

16:27.000 --> 16:28.708
Um..

16:28.708 --> 16:31.667
...I also have a,
a favor to ask.

16:31.667 --> 16:33.084
Again.

16:34.166 --> 16:36.417
What's the favor?

16:36.417 --> 16:38.959
You remember
my roomie Savannah?

16:38.959 --> 16:42.291
Her dad's in big trouble,
and he needs a lawyer.

16:43.458 --> 16:46.167
But they can't exactly
pay you.

16:47.291 --> 16:48.875
Well, if this gets me
out of trouble

16:48.875 --> 16:50.125
for not mentioning
my wife or my kid--

16:50.125 --> 16:54.167
- Absolutely. Mm-hmm.
- Then I'm in.

16:54.167 --> 16:56.125
How soon can they meet?

16:56.125 --> 16:58.917
(Julian)
'Your husband was skimming
the interest from the bonds'

16:58.917 --> 17:01.750
'that were intended
for infrastructure projects.'

17:01.750 --> 17:05.125
'The banks made so much money
off the sky-high interest'

17:05.125 --> 17:07.040
'from the synthetic rate
swap scheme'

17:07.040 --> 17:09.583
that they bribed
city officials

17:09.583 --> 17:12.165
into rubber-stamping
all the deals.

17:12.165 --> 17:14.416
'And that,
along with related crimes'

17:14.416 --> 17:17.208
'is what Parker's
being charged with.'

17:20.500 --> 17:22.916
Do you have any questions?

17:25.750 --> 17:27.208
Can you get our dad
out of jail?

17:27.208 --> 17:29.209
Parker was arraigned
this morning

17:29.209 --> 17:32.000
and the judge granted bail
in the amount of $50,000.

17:32.000 --> 17:34.291
Great.
We can handle that, right?

17:34.291 --> 17:36.792
Our accounts have been
frozen, sweetheart.

17:36.792 --> 17:39.500
- They have?
- Yes.

17:39.500 --> 17:41.042
Charlotte, haven't
you been listening?

17:41.042 --> 17:42.208
Are you thick?

17:42.208 --> 17:43.708
[scoffs]

17:43.708 --> 17:46.458
For the record, that nasty
comment about your mommy

17:46.458 --> 17:48.042
was made by Aunt Savannah.

17:48.042 --> 17:49.500
- You know what, knock it off.
- Aunt Savannah!

17:49.500 --> 17:52.708
Girls, please.
I have a severe headache.

17:55.125 --> 17:56.583
[exhales]

17:56.583 --> 17:59.708
Now, Mr. Parrish,
what other options do we have?

17:59.708 --> 18:01.208
Well, I will be working on
getting you

18:01.208 --> 18:02.583
an allowance from the court.

18:02.583 --> 18:04.000
And I will also make a motion

18:04.000 --> 18:06.750
to get the bail reduced,
but there's a very good chance

18:06.750 --> 18:09.042
that the judge
will not allow that

18:09.042 --> 18:10.542
'so, you're gonna have
to get a loan'

18:10.542 --> 18:13.167
or work something out
with a bail bondsman.

18:13.167 --> 18:15.333
Well, I have tried that,
but without collateral

18:15.333 --> 18:17.166
they will not lend us a penny.

18:17.166 --> 18:19.625
- Mom, you could
ask the church.
- Oh, don't be ridiculous.

18:19.625 --> 18:21.750
- Yeah, the Angel Fund.
- Angel Fund?

18:21.750 --> 18:24.542
They use it to help members
of the church in trouble

18:24.542 --> 18:26.542
you know,
if someone's in danger
of losing their house.

18:26.542 --> 18:28.542
That fund is not
for people like us.

18:28.542 --> 18:30.583
We are not having
mortgage trouble.

18:30.583 --> 18:33.500
You happen to have a father
who is an accused felon.

18:33.500 --> 18:35.834
- Wrongly accused.
- Yeah.

18:35.834 --> 18:38.625
You don't really
believe that dad really
took bribes, do you?

18:38.625 --> 18:40.125
Well, of course not, honey.

18:40.125 --> 18:44.458
Mom, you have to talk
to Pastor George, okay?

18:44.458 --> 18:46.792
Dad has given
his life to that church.

18:46.792 --> 18:48.667
You're on
the board of directors.

18:48.667 --> 18:50.209
Yeah, and
it's just a bail.

18:50.209 --> 18:51.291
They'll get it back
eventually.

18:54.375 --> 18:58.542
Uh, what other moves
do we have, Mr. Parrish?

18:58.542 --> 19:01.375
Well, just let me say
if you can convince
your church

19:01.375 --> 19:03.792
to give you the bail money..

19:03.792 --> 19:06.042
...you should jump at it.

19:07.084 --> 19:10.209
That is, assuming
you want Parker home.

19:10.209 --> 19:12.458
Well, of course I do.

19:14.417 --> 19:16.750
I will talk to Pastor George.

19:23.750 --> 19:26.542
[instrumental music]

19:30.583 --> 19:33.125
♪ Crank it up ♪

19:33.125 --> 19:34.750
♪ Crank it up now ♪

19:34.750 --> 19:37.542
♪ Hey hey hey ♪
♪ Crank it up ♪

19:37.542 --> 19:40.167
♪ Crank it up now ♪
♪ Crank it up ♪

19:40.167 --> 19:42.542
♪ My mama didn't raise
no quitter son ♪

19:42.542 --> 19:44.500
♪ We ain't leavin'
until we're done ♪

19:44.500 --> 19:47.417
♪ Yeah yeah crank it up ♪

19:47.417 --> 19:50.209
♪ Crank it up now ♪

19:50.209 --> 19:52.333
♪ Crank it up ♪

19:52.333 --> 19:54.041
♪ Crank it up now ♪

19:54.041 --> 19:56.000
♪ Alright ♪

19:57.208 --> 19:58.583
♪ Crank it up ♪

19:58.583 --> 20:00.208
[cheering]

20:00.208 --> 20:03.042
[groans]

20:03.042 --> 20:05.208
Oh, hey, hey.
I'll get some ice.

20:05.208 --> 20:08.000
(The Madman)
'Alright, boys and girls,
that's a five-minute break.'

20:08.000 --> 20:11.125
Just enough time
to change them diapers,
alright? Alright.

20:11.125 --> 20:13.083
[electro dance music]

20:18.208 --> 20:21.250
Oh. How's that knee
holding up?

20:21.250 --> 20:24.417
- It's fine.
- Hm. Now, maybe.

20:24.417 --> 20:26.750
You've still got
19 hours to go.

20:30.500 --> 20:32.000
I'm not gonna bail on Lewis.

20:32.000 --> 20:35.375
He wants that car for his dad,
and I'm gonna help him win it.

20:35.375 --> 20:37.083
Yeah, it'd be a damn shame

20:37.083 --> 20:39.959
if you had to drop out
with a ruined knee.

20:39.959 --> 20:41.083
You'd have
to sit out nationals.

20:41.083 --> 20:43.375
Wait. Wait.
Who's sitting out
nationals?

20:43.375 --> 20:46.000
Her knee.
It's not so good.

20:47.041 --> 20:49.125
Let me see. Oh, no.

20:49.125 --> 20:52.792
No, we...we can't push this.
We're, we're dropping out.

20:52.792 --> 20:55.333
- We're just dropping out.
- What about the car?

20:55.333 --> 20:57.125
I'll just figure
something else out.

20:57.125 --> 21:00.208
I'm-I'm actually
without a partner.

21:00.208 --> 21:01.291
- What?
- Yeah.

21:01.291 --> 21:02.917
Morgan punked out on me.

21:02.917 --> 21:06.125
I was just gonna go home
and cut my losses, but..

21:06.125 --> 21:09.041
...I, I'd like to
help your dad.

21:09.041 --> 21:11.708
If you'll have me, that is.

21:16.000 --> 21:17.917
You want it.

21:17.917 --> 21:20.083
You wanna dance
with her.

21:21.959 --> 21:23.417
I just wanna
help out my dad.

21:23.417 --> 21:27.000
- Screw your dad.
- Screw my dad?

21:27.000 --> 21:29.708
I'm sorry, but seriously,
what are you, Alice's lap dog?

21:29.708 --> 21:32.375
No. Look, Kathy, you..

21:32.375 --> 21:35.250
You do not wanna be
talking to me like that.

21:35.250 --> 21:37.084
If you dance
with Alice, you have

21:37.084 --> 21:40.167
maybe a two percent chance
of winning that car

21:40.167 --> 21:43.917
and a 100% chance
of losing me.
You understand me?

21:43.917 --> 21:47.166
If I wanna dance with Alice,
I'll dance with her.

21:47.166 --> 21:49.166
Do you understand me?

21:52.500 --> 21:54.834
I hope you break something.

21:58.583 --> 22:00.042
That was mean.

22:00.042 --> 22:02.042
Don't be over here
playing all innocent, okay?

22:02.042 --> 22:03.542
When I was over there
getting ice

22:03.542 --> 22:07.041
you were over here working
on her, winding her up.

22:07.041 --> 22:08.708
You see me denying it?

22:08.708 --> 22:11.667
(The Madman)
'Dancers, back
on the floor! Alright..'

22:11.667 --> 22:14.417
Look, the way I see it,
you've got two options.

22:14.417 --> 22:17.875
You can go running
after Nasty Kathy.

22:17.875 --> 22:20.125
With her gimpy knee, I'm sure
she'll be easy to catch.

22:20.125 --> 22:22.500
Or you can take my hand.

22:22.500 --> 22:23.834
Now, which option do you think

22:23.834 --> 22:26.125
puts your dad behind
the wheel of that RAV4?

22:29.041 --> 22:30.750
Ugh.

22:32.125 --> 22:35.000
You, you are a piece of work.

22:35.000 --> 22:37.333
A piece of work that's gonna
tear up the dance floor.

22:37.333 --> 22:39.167
Come on. Go tell them
about the partner change.

22:39.167 --> 22:42.084
- Don't wanna
get disqualified.
- See you out there.

22:44.083 --> 22:46.417
[groans]

22:46.417 --> 22:48.083
Oh, God.

22:50.167 --> 22:51.959
You.

22:51.959 --> 22:54.000
- You're fired.
- What?

23:00.625 --> 23:02.917
Oh. Thank you.

23:06.084 --> 23:09.125
So? Have you talked
to Pastor George?

23:09.125 --> 23:12.084
Is the Angel Fund gonna
give us the bail money?

23:14.250 --> 23:16.000
I haven't asked.

23:17.375 --> 23:19.167
Well..

23:19.917 --> 23:21.291
...when are you going to?

23:21.291 --> 23:24.834
Our church members read the
paper like everybody else.

23:24.834 --> 23:27.000
How exactly am I supposed
to convince them

23:27.000 --> 23:28.750
your father
isn't a lying cheat?

23:28.750 --> 23:31.834
It's a church. I'd hope
they'd take it on faith.

23:31.834 --> 23:34.041
Why should they? I don't.

23:35.209 --> 23:37.708
Mom...no.

23:37.708 --> 23:39.625
Look..

23:39.625 --> 23:43.166
Life did not turn out for your
father the way he had planned.

23:44.625 --> 23:46.000
He always thought
he was entitled

23:46.000 --> 23:48.959
to more money, better job,
bigger house.

23:48.959 --> 23:52.500
Now, don't get me wrong,
sweetie, I do love him

23:52.500 --> 23:55.291
but he has never
been satisfied
with his lot in life.

23:55.291 --> 23:58.084
If he thought others
were opening doors for him

23:58.084 --> 24:01.125
leading him to the life
he deserved, well..

24:01.959 --> 24:03.542
...I have to wonder.

24:04.875 --> 24:07.000
What you're saying is
disgusting and disloyal.

24:07.000 --> 24:12.084
Don't you lash out at me.
I am simply trying
to be honest.

24:12.084 --> 24:15.667
We have to get dad out
of jail, no matter what.

24:15.667 --> 24:18.167
We can't give up on him.

24:18.167 --> 24:20.750
He'd be there for us.

24:20.750 --> 24:23.417
Wouldn't he?
Be there for us?

24:27.000 --> 24:29.458
Give me the stupid phone.

24:35.333 --> 24:37.458
I raised you right.

24:37.458 --> 24:40.458
And quite honestly,
it's a real pain.

24:43.250 --> 24:44.917
[sighs]

24:44.917 --> 24:48.041
Sally, how are you?
Layne Monroe here.

24:48.041 --> 24:52.625
Yes, I-I was hoping
to have a, a few words
with Pastor George.

24:52.625 --> 24:54.083
[laughs]

24:54.083 --> 24:57.792
One minute, y'all got
one minute to get back
to the dance floor

24:57.792 --> 25:00.125
or you are O-U-T, out.

25:03.834 --> 25:06.167
Hey, you ready to get
back out there, huh?

25:06.167 --> 25:09.959
Yeah. Just sitting here,
scoping out the competition.

25:09.959 --> 25:12.125
Oh. You okay?

25:12.125 --> 25:15.209
Yeah. Just should've
worn more comfortable
shoes. Come on.

25:15.209 --> 25:17.083
Come on, come on,
come on. Let's go,

25:17.083 --> 25:18.375
let's go, let's go, people.

25:18.375 --> 25:20.250
Ain't no rest in
this particular
circle of hell.

25:20.250 --> 25:21.250
Come on, now.

