28:47.083 --> 28:48.208
Oh.

28:48.208 --> 28:49.291
'Where's the fire
extinguisher?'

28:49.291 --> 28:52.125
(Julian)
'In the closet.'

28:52.125 --> 28:55.208
(Julian)
'Well, my kitchen looks
and smells like burnt toast.'

28:56.708 --> 29:01.125
Yes, I am making a list for
the insurance claim right now.

29:01.125 --> 29:05.625
No, I was alone. I just
got distracted, that's all.

29:05.625 --> 29:08.125
Look, I gotta go.
I'll call you back. Bye.

29:09.166 --> 29:10.625
Insurance company?

29:10.625 --> 29:13.041
Mm-hmm.

29:13.041 --> 29:15.959
You really think your agent
cares you had a girl over?

29:15.959 --> 29:18.083
I just thought
it would be simpler.

29:18.083 --> 29:20.708
Oh, you chose poorly.

29:20.708 --> 29:22.166
Why is that?

29:22.166 --> 29:26.792
See, insurance is a personal
aphrodisiac of mine.

29:26.792 --> 29:27.917
Oh, it is now.

29:27.917 --> 29:30.042
It's a little-known quirk.

29:30.042 --> 29:33.583
Wanda overflowed our bathtub,
and this nice claims adjuster

29:33.583 --> 29:35.875
replaced her
whole shoe collection.

29:35.875 --> 29:37.000
Hmm.

29:37.000 --> 29:41.000
It drove me absolutely crazy.

29:41.000 --> 29:42.417
Are we still talking
about insurance?

29:42.417 --> 29:44.875
I never stopped talking
about insurance.

29:48.708 --> 29:50.834
[cell phone beeps]

29:50.834 --> 29:53.333
[sighs]

29:54.125 --> 29:56.500
Oh. Duty calls.

29:59.417 --> 30:01.083
Damn it.

30:03.084 --> 30:05.125
Nope. That's all you get.

30:16.375 --> 30:17.708
Girls.

30:18.542 --> 30:20.041
[buzzer buzzing]

30:20.041 --> 30:22.209
- Dad.
- Oh, dad!

30:22.209 --> 30:23.500
Oh.

30:25.250 --> 30:27.166
Thank God. Thank God.
You got me out of there.

30:27.166 --> 30:28.500
Thank the Angel Fund.

30:28.500 --> 30:31.667
The baby missed you.
Here, he's kicking.

30:34.250 --> 30:36.750
I felt it.
I felt him kick.

30:36.750 --> 30:38.750
Come on, dad.
Let's get you home.

30:38.750 --> 30:40.750
The sooner, the better.

30:44.125 --> 30:47.458
[Smokey Robinson
singing "Going To A Go-Go"]

30:51.834 --> 30:54.041
(The Madman)
'Come on now. Come on now.'

30:54.041 --> 30:57.125
What you got?
What y'all got? Come on.

30:57.125 --> 30:59.583
♪ Going to a go-go ♪
♪ Na-na-na ♪

30:59.583 --> 31:02.542
'Oh, snap.
Bye-bye, sugarpie.'

31:02.542 --> 31:04.333
'Too bad, y'all have to go.
Three couples left.'

31:04.333 --> 31:06.625
'Three minutes. Come on.'

31:09.042 --> 31:11.959
Hey, Raggedy Annie,
Annie, hey!

31:11.959 --> 31:15.792
Y'all got to go
with that. Come on now.
You gotta clean it up.

31:15.792 --> 31:18.083
♪ Going to a go-go ♪

31:18.083 --> 31:21.167
♪ Everybody's ♪
♪ Going to a go-go ♪

31:21.167 --> 31:23.792
♪ Come on now.. ♪

31:23.792 --> 31:25.917
We so got this now.

31:28.125 --> 31:30.125
Okay. Okay.
Two couples, one car!

31:30.125 --> 31:31.792
We gotta do
something different.

31:31.792 --> 31:34.291
Come on, Ms. Ciara, what you
think we should do, girl?

31:34.291 --> 31:37.417
You know what,
I think we speed
this thing all the way up.

31:37.417 --> 31:38.792
I think so.
Come on, y'all.
What y'all think?

31:38.792 --> 31:40.291
- Yeah.
- Yes!

31:40.291 --> 31:43.125
[Jessie And The Toy Boys
singing "Sing Sing Sing"]

31:43.125 --> 31:45.458
One minute warning.
Come on, now.

31:48.166 --> 31:50.250
♪ Sing sing sing sing ♪

31:50.250 --> 31:52.291
♪ Everybody start to sing ♪

31:52.291 --> 31:54.542
♪ Swing swing swing swing ♪

31:54.542 --> 31:56.792
♪ Everybody start to swing ♪

31:56.792 --> 31:58.500
[scatting]

31:58.500 --> 32:01.750
♪ Now you're singing
while you swing ♪

32:11.708 --> 32:14.209
[no audio]

32:14.209 --> 32:16.667
(The Madman)
Look at that!

32:25.708 --> 32:27.792
[scatting]

32:30.583 --> 32:32.166
- Give me a boost.
- Are you crazy?

32:32.166 --> 32:34.291
Just do it.

32:35.250 --> 32:37.625
[scatting continues]

32:39.000 --> 32:41.458
'Whoo!'

32:43.750 --> 32:45.792
Oh, no! Oh, no! Oh, no!

32:45.792 --> 32:48.375
[scatting continues]

32:52.667 --> 32:54.917
[crowd cheering]

32:58.500 --> 33:00.125
(The Madman)
'Oh. Uh!'

33:00.125 --> 33:03.125
'Oh, yeah! Yeah! Oh.'

33:03.125 --> 33:06.250
So, looks like
we have a winner.

33:06.250 --> 33:09.167
Couple number 273.

33:09.167 --> 33:12.167
[cheering]

33:12.167 --> 33:13.834
Come get your keys!

33:15.208 --> 33:16.500
Oh, thank you.

33:16.500 --> 33:17.708
Good job, brother.

33:17.708 --> 33:20.542
Good job. Good job, man.
Good job, y'all.

33:23.125 --> 33:24.625
(Lewis)
'Oh, my God.'

33:24.625 --> 33:27.167
Oh, it-it's not
as bad as it looks.

33:27.167 --> 33:29.708
- I'll be fine by nationals--
- You should've
said something.

33:29.708 --> 33:31.917
No sense in complaining
if you're not planning
on quitting.

33:31.917 --> 33:33.625
Okay. We gotta
get these feet
taken care of.

33:33.625 --> 33:37.041
No. I-I need...some time.

33:37.041 --> 33:39.125
[sighs]

33:39.125 --> 33:40.917
I got it.

33:42.166 --> 33:43.917
I got it.

33:45.208 --> 33:47.041
Come on.

33:47.041 --> 33:49.667
[instrumental music]

34:00.333 --> 34:02.125
Still dealing
with insurance stuff?

34:02.125 --> 34:04.250
Uh, actually, just started.

34:04.250 --> 34:06.792
What will they think of next?

34:06.792 --> 34:09.083
Insurance agent
in your pocket?

34:09.083 --> 34:12.291
Actually, it's like having
two agents in your pocket.

34:13.625 --> 34:16.042
You must have big pockets.

34:16.042 --> 34:17.833
You have no idea.

34:17.833 --> 34:19.583
[sighs]

34:19.583 --> 34:22.250
So here's the thing,
counselor.

34:23.166 --> 34:25.667
If you just started
the process

34:25.667 --> 34:28.208
who were you on the phone
with this morning?

34:32.875 --> 34:35.208
My ex. Correction.

34:35.208 --> 34:37.542
My soon-to-be ex.

34:40.000 --> 34:42.000
Okay.

34:42.000 --> 34:44.333
You lied to me. Why?

34:45.792 --> 34:48.208
Self-conscious.

34:48.208 --> 34:50.750
A little embarrassed.

34:50.750 --> 34:54.250
You really know how
to make a girl feel special.

34:54.250 --> 34:57.792
Come on, Marti.
Take a look at yourself.

34:57.792 --> 34:59.834
You're like an advertisement
for a male's mid-life crisis.

34:59.834 --> 35:01.750
When we walk down
the street together

35:01.750 --> 35:05.209
onlookers probably think
I've just purchased a Porsche.

35:05.209 --> 35:08.042
You're not dating onlookers.
You're dating me.

35:10.208 --> 35:12.792
What's important
is how you see me.

35:15.084 --> 35:16.542
'So tell me.'

35:18.667 --> 35:21.875
- Tell you what exactly--
- 'How do you see me?'

35:21.875 --> 35:24.250
What is it
you-you like about me?

35:27.209 --> 35:29.291
Why are you in this?

35:30.417 --> 35:33.084
Is this a challenge?

35:35.291 --> 35:37.000
[sighs]

35:38.583 --> 35:41.125
You are a fascinating

35:41.125 --> 35:43.667
occasionally maddening woman.

35:46.125 --> 35:48.959
You have a quicksilver mind
and a gigantic heart.

35:49.834 --> 35:51.834
You love your friends
to a fault

35:51.834 --> 35:55.084
'and you despise injustice
with a white-hot intensity.'

35:55.084 --> 35:57.834
You resist authority, not
because you're an anarchist

35:57.834 --> 35:59.250
but because..

35:59.250 --> 36:01.834
...you're a leader by nature.

36:03.792 --> 36:06.583
And you refuse to be bullied,
and you will not allow me

36:06.583 --> 36:09.708
to win an argument
if you know you're right.

36:12.084 --> 36:14.959
And you're not afraid
to laugh at yourself.

36:17.667 --> 36:22.167
And you're a slightly,
slightly better guitar
player than I am.

36:25.208 --> 36:30.500
And that, Marti Perkins,
is but a small sampling

36:30.500 --> 36:33.084
of the things
I like about you.

36:38.125 --> 36:41.166
Oh. Okay.

36:41.166 --> 36:44.333
[instrumental music]

37:17.333 --> 37:19.583
I heard your dad's
out on bail.

37:20.458 --> 37:22.875
I'm glad to hear it.

37:22.875 --> 37:25.500
- I bet.
- I am.

37:25.500 --> 37:28.375
Look, I'm sorry
about the other day.

37:28.375 --> 37:32.458
I was upset, and I shot
my mouth off in a bad way.

37:34.667 --> 37:36.209
It's okay.

37:37.417 --> 37:41.375
Look, I'm propping up
my whole family right now.

37:41.375 --> 37:43.667
I need to know
I can depend on you.

37:46.167 --> 37:47.625
Understood.

37:49.041 --> 37:52.291
Go ahead. Depend.

37:53.125 --> 37:55.000
[cell phone rings]

37:55.000 --> 37:57.000
- It's my dad.
- Yeah.

37:57.000 --> 38:00.000
Hey, daddy,
everything okay at home?

38:00.000 --> 38:03.375
(Parker)
'I couldn't leave
without saying goodbye.'

38:03.375 --> 38:07.042
Goodbye?
What are you talking about?

38:07.042 --> 38:08.083
Sweetheart, I have made
some mistakes

38:08.083 --> 38:10.750
and I cannot make them
right in prison

38:10.750 --> 38:13.125
and I can't-I can't
go back there.

38:14.458 --> 38:15.667
Oh, God.

38:15.667 --> 38:17.834
'I am so sorry
for letting you down'

38:17.834 --> 38:20.542
'but I am gonna win back
your trust someday.'

38:20.542 --> 38:22.000
Now, look, you have
to take care of your mother

38:22.000 --> 38:23.458
and you have to take care
of your sister.

38:23.458 --> 38:26.625
They are gonna need
your strength right now.

38:26.625 --> 38:28.500
You can't.

38:28.500 --> 38:30.625
You're going to ruin us.

38:30.625 --> 38:33.208
Please, daddy, don't.

38:33.208 --> 38:35.917
I love you, sweet,
I love you, sweetheart.

38:38.917 --> 38:40.041
[sobbing]

38:40.041 --> 38:43.042
Hey, what's going on?
What happened?

